text: Morristown is a town of Morris County in the state of New Jersey, United States. About 20,180 people were living in Morristown as of the year 2020. It is the county seat of Morris County. Morristown has an area of 3 square miles. During the American Revolutionary War it was twice the winter quarters of George Washington and his Continental Army. == References == == Other websites == *Morristown municipal website Category:County seats in New Jersey Category:Towns in New Jersey
